{A number of super tournaments in Madrid started with a fascist event that
lasted from 4 until 22 x 1943. Fifteen men participated. They battled for
eight prizes. The Spanish chess prodigy Pomar took part. Keres was the main
player. As a chess professional, his income depended on such events. We follow
his games and one game by Pomar.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Nf6 5.
