12. Re2 g5 13. a3 Be7 {They play a sharp line of the Two Knights.} 14. Bg3 $5 (
14. b4 {happened in Romanovsky - Belavenets, Leningrad/Moscow 1939.}) 14...
O-O-O 15. b4 Qd5 16. Qe1 h5 $5 17. h4 Bg4 18. c4 Qf5 19. b5 Bxf3 20. bxc6 d3 $2
{Keres lets his edge slip.} ({Better is} 20... b6 $1 21. Bxc7 Bxe2 {
and Black has a great advantage.}) 21. cxb7+ Kb8 $5 22. Bxc7+ $1 Kxc7 23. Ng3
dxe2 {Black delivers a semi-sacrifice.} 24. Nxf5 Rd1 $1 25. Nxe7 Rxe1+ 26. Rxe1
Bxb7 $5 27. Rxe2 gxh4 28. Kh2 Rd8 29. Nf5 Bc8 30. Re5 Rd2 31. f3 h3 $6 32. Kxh3
Rd3 $6 ({Preferable is} 32... Bd7 33. Re7 Ra2) 33. a4 Bd7 34. a5 Rc3 35. Rc5+
Kd8 36. Kh4 Bxf5 37. Rxf5 Rxc4+ 38. Kxh5 {
White has an extra pawn in the rook endgame.} Ke7 39. Rb5 Kf6 40. g3 Ra4 41. f4
Ra3 {Medina could try to utilise his plus.} 1/2-1/2

